Class FilterIpAddressesTableModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.table.AbstractTableModel

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.table.TableModel

    public class FilterIpAddressesTableModel
extends DataTableModel<FilterIpAddressesTableModel.AppIPAddressSelection>
    Represents the table model for the Select Applications/IPs dialog (accessed from the View menu) that allows the user to filter the trace information based on application name or IP address.

        public javax.swing.table.TableColumnModel createDefaultTableColumnModel()
        Returns a TableColumnModel that is based on the default table column model for the DataTableModel class. The TableColumnModel returned by this method has the same number of columns in the same order and structure as the table column model in the DataTableModel. When a DataTable object is created, this method is used to create the TableColumnModel if one is not specified. This method may be overridden in order to provide customizations to the default column model, such as providing a default column width and/or adding column renderers and editors.
